A java webapp is an archive containing static resources, application code and configuration.
This example will only contain one static resource (index.html).

Build with: jar cf webapp.war index.html
            (or zip webapp.war index.html)

Run with: Copy or move the webapp.war into ${TOMCAT_HOME}/webapps
          Start tomcat - ${TOMCAT_HOME}/bin/catalina.sh run
          Open http://localhost:8080/webapp in a browser
